<h3>Google's Closure Dialogs</h3>

Closure's Dialogs are replacements for JavaScript's alert() and prompt(). They are to say the least cumbersome to set-up and you also need to watch your CSS, in order for them to perform properly. 

My own view is that jQuery's UI dialogs are much superior and easier to set-up.  Applications do use a number of dialogs and my suggestion in such a case is that you do collect them in a separate file to make their management easier.

